news.title: Lower mortgage rates boost US home sales in February
news.para: The jump in sales of previously owned homes, which was reported by the National Association of Realtors on Tuesday, was the largest in more than 2-1/2 years and ended 12 straight monthly declines in sales, the longest such stretch since 1999.

news.title: Now, government employees can buy plots in smart townships across Andhra Pradesh
news.para: This will help employees purchase sites in layouts developed by urban development authorities anywhere in the state irrespective of the district they are working.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to bring unassessed buildings under property tax ambit in a year
news.para: According to a KMC revenue department official, mayor Firhad Hakim has instructed the department to make all assessment department officials accountable for assessment of unassessed buildings and arrange for mutation of properties.

news.title: Kolbro group appointed for GIS-mapping of urban land in Goa
news.para: Nagpur-based project management and GIS consultant for government bodies M/s Kolbro group pvt ltd has been tasked by GSUDA to execute the mapping.

news.title: Dharavi redevelopment: Maharashtra says LoI to be issued only after financial capability is established
news.para: ​​He was replying after Congress MLA Varsha Gaikwad, whose constituency includes Dharavi, raised concerns about the project in the wake of Hindenburg Research's allegations of stock manipulation against the Adani group.

news.title: SC says shouldn't disturb common areas at Amrapali approved earlier
news.para: A bench of Justices Ajay Rastogi and Bela M Trivedi, which is exploring various options to raise funds to complete the project, said that whatever facilities and common areas which were approved should not be disturbed.

news.title: Casagrand forays into commercial real estate, to invest Rs 8,000 over next five years
news.para: The commercial development will be undertaken under its subsidiary company Casagrand Commercial. The company aims to develop 10mn sq ft of commercial and retail spaces by 2027, which has an estimated rental potential of Rs 900 Cr annually.

news.title: Homebuyers concerned over no representation in West Bengal RERA implementation committee
news.para: The state government had last week constituted a nine-member West Bengal State Working Committee on WBRERA. The committee includes two members from the state government’s housing department, three from the West Bengal real estate regulatory authority and four real estate developers operating in the state.

news.title: WTCA join hands with Merlin Group to develop World Trade Centre in Kolkata
news.para: Merlin Group is looking at an investment of Rs 1,500 crore for the development of World Trade Centre project in the Nabadiganta Industrial Township Authority (NDITA) area, Salt Lake, Kolkata

news.title: Tamil Nadu: Guideline value revision annuls gain of registration fee cut
news.para: The halving of property registration charges from 4% to 2%, while restoring the pre-2017 guideline value for properties, will result in several spinoff benefits though immediate home-buyers will have to pay more.

news.title: Jaipur: UD tax collection picks up pace as March 31 deadline approaches
news.para: JMC Heritage officials said that reminder calls are being made to regular tax payers, camps are being set up in every zone, and special camps have been set up to collect the tax from marriage gardens, which owe a major amount.

news.title: Secunderabad: SCB aims to fix funds crunch through property tax windfall
news.para: There are at least 30,000 residential and commercial properties, as per records, and the SCB tax wing had taken up marathon exercise to recover tax and served demand notices on defaulters.

news.title: Indore development body's fair to sell over 800 flats at five-year-old rate begins
news.para: IDA chairman Jaypal Singh Chawda said the authority has a total 808 ready for possession flats in its apartments in Scheme 155 near Sangam Nagar in the low and middle-income group categories.

news.title: Bidhannagar civic body plans 10% fine, 10% interest on property tax dues till March 31
news.para: This was discussed on Monday as the BMC presented its full budget for 2023-24. The authorities showed a proposed surplus budget of Rs 49 lakh with an income of Rs 423.5 crore and expenditure of Rs 423 crore.

news.title: Varanasi development body stops plotting of 64 illegal colonies
news.para: On Monday a team of the VDA led by junior secretary Devchandra Ram, zonal officer Chandrabhan Dixit and junior engineer RK Singh raided Singhpur area along the ring road and demolished boundaries of plots in 17 bigha land developed by Prabhunarain and Mahendra Gautam.
